1
00:00:00,120 --> 00:00:02,280
I think…I’m falling for someone.

2
00:00:03,720 --> 00:00:05,520
I also have someone that I like.

3
00:00:06,240 --> 00:00:07,520
Someone told me to give this to you.

4
00:00:07,520 --> 00:00:09,000
It must come from the same person

5
00:00:09,000 --> 00:00:10,200
who left you the note.

6
00:00:10,920 --> 00:00:12,960
Why did you cheer on our opponent team?

7
00:00:13,880 --> 00:00:15,200
Don’t you think this is too much?

8
00:00:17,680 --> 00:00:19,400
He scores a goal.

9
00:00:22,280 --> 00:00:22,840
Here.

10
00:00:23,080 --> 00:00:25,000
A reward for a hero.

11
00:00:25,880 --> 00:00:26,760
Thanks.

12
00:00:33,480 --> 00:00:35,560
(The most valuable thing is time.)

13
00:00:37,800 --> 00:00:40,160
(We are halfway through our high school life.)

14
00:00:40,320 --> 00:00:44,120
(To get to know a person is to understand their world.)

15
00:00:45,600 --> 00:00:46,360
I’ll take this desk.

16
00:00:49,800 --> 00:00:50,480
Hi.

17
00:00:50,800 --> 00:00:53,560
Tle, you are wearing braces.

18
00:00:54,360 --> 00:00:56,040
I’ve been wearing them since last year.

19
00:00:56,480 --> 00:00:57,440
Is that so?

20
00:00:57,760 --> 00:00:59,520
Sorry, I’m busy with my own stuff.

21
00:00:59,600 --> 00:01:01,920
So I don’t pay much attention
to other people’s lives.

22
00:01:02,760 --> 00:01:08,120
(It takes around 200 hours
for a friendship to grow into a close one.)

23
00:01:08,120 --> 00:01:09,000
Achi, hit me.

24
00:01:09,360 --> 00:01:09,760
No.
Come on. Hit me.

25
00:01:10,760 --> 00:01:11,920
Why do I need to do that?

26
00:01:11,920 --> 00:01:13,680
Achi, you’re killing the fun.

27
00:01:14,200 --> 00:01:14,760
Fine.

28
00:01:14,960 --> 00:01:17,640
Ouch! Achi, it hurts.

29
00:01:17,640 --> 00:01:23,720
(If you want to cross the friend zone,
theoretically, it takes around 2 – 4 months.)

30
00:01:24,680 --> 00:01:26,920
Ko Neung, Ko Song is not here yet?

31
00:01:28,840 --> 00:01:33,960
(Surprisingly, it takes only 7 seconds to fall for someone.)

32
00:01:40,600 --> 00:01:44,760
(The person who makes me realize this is this guy.)

33
00:03:11,240 --> 00:03:13,320
You look different when you wear glasses.

34
00:03:14,200 --> 00:03:16,400
You look cool, calm, and charming.

35
00:03:18,160 --> 00:03:19,560
Ko Song, you are short-sighted?

36
00:03:20,160 --> 00:03:22,080
Yes, a little.
I’m worried that I can’t see the blackboard.

37
00:03:22,520 --> 00:03:23,960
But I’m wearing glasses only in class.

38
00:03:24,640 --> 00:03:27,280
Let me take a good look at you.

39
00:03:27,680 --> 00:03:28,680
What are you doing?

40
00:03:29,920 --> 00:03:32,680
I want to see if you look more handsome,
like they say.

41
00:03:34,480 --> 00:03:35,240
So?

42
00:03:51,400 --> 00:03:52,200
Not really.

43
00:03:58,200 --> 00:04:00,640
I spent the school break
at my house in another province.

44
00:04:00,640 --> 00:04:01,480
When I get back,

45
00:04:02,080 --> 00:04:04,040
you all look different.

46
00:04:04,160 --> 00:04:05,120
You’re right.

47
00:04:05,480 --> 00:04:07,480
You guys have changed a lot.

48
00:04:08,040 --> 00:04:09,200
Ko Song is wearing glasses.

49
00:04:10,080 --> 00:04:11,320
Augar is now a school athlete.

50
00:04:11,680 --> 00:04:13,800
Achi got a new phone.

51
00:04:14,720 --> 00:04:16,160
August…

52
00:04:18,200 --> 00:04:19,960
I’m taking my studies seriously now.

53
00:04:21,520 --> 00:04:22,200
Fine.

54
00:04:23,200 --> 00:04:25,760
But why am I still the same?

55
00:04:27,600 --> 00:04:30,160
Then you should start paying attention in class.

56
00:04:31,600 --> 00:04:34,120
If you don’t like studying,
why don’t you find something that you like?

57
00:04:39,800 --> 00:04:40,760
I found it.

58
00:04:42,800 --> 00:04:43,720
What I like.

59
00:05:02,440 --> 00:05:03,200
This.

60
00:05:03,320 --> 00:05:04,400
I like eating.

61
00:05:10,000 --> 00:05:10,760
What?

62
00:05:12,920 --> 00:05:14,360
Do you want to have some?

63
00:05:26,040 --> 00:05:27,520
What are you doing?

64
00:05:29,240 --> 00:05:31,200
Are you wearing perfume to school?

65
00:05:36,640 --> 00:05:38,080
Is the scent that strong?

66
00:05:38,400 --> 00:05:39,560
No, it’s a light scent.

67
00:05:40,040 --> 00:05:42,560
But if I get closer, the scent will be stronger.

68
00:05:56,320 --> 00:05:58,480
Here, here, right here.

69
00:05:58,880 --> 00:05:59,800
The scent is strong.

70
00:06:01,920 --> 00:06:03,920
Do you like it?

71
00:06:10,880 --> 00:06:13,280
Yes, it smells good.

72
00:06:33,560 --> 00:06:35,440
Hey, come here. I saved a spot for you.

73
00:06:36,560 --> 00:06:39,080
Sorry. My friend saved a spot for me.

74
00:06:41,080 --> 00:06:42,120
What will we order?

75
00:06:43,320 --> 00:06:45,480
Augar, do we still have a practice this evening?

76
00:06:51,240 --> 00:06:53,120
Achi, you haven’t had lunch?

77
00:06:53,920 --> 00:06:54,840
The cafeteria is crowded.

78
00:06:55,320 --> 00:06:56,240
Hey, I’m here.

79
00:06:56,640 --> 00:06:59,040
The teacher dismisses my class so late.

80
00:06:59,040 --> 00:06:59,760
Yes, so late.
Excuse me.

81
00:07:01,360 --> 00:07:01,920
Yes.

82
00:07:02,200 --> 00:07:03,200
There is a line.

83
00:07:03,880 --> 00:07:05,280
Why aren’t you lining up?

84
00:07:06,560 --> 00:07:07,640
Many people are waiting in line.

85
00:07:09,120 --> 00:07:11,080
Don’t you feel any shame
about cutting the line?

86
00:07:11,080 --> 00:07:12,000
Easy.

87
00:07:12,520 --> 00:07:14,680
I saved spots in the line for my friends.

88
00:07:14,680 --> 00:07:16,160
What about others waiting in line?

89
00:07:16,160 --> 00:07:17,080
Don’t be so serious about it?

90
00:07:17,080 --> 00:07:18,520
That’s right.

91
00:07:19,600 --> 00:07:21,120
I think you should go to the back of the line.

92
00:07:22,120 --> 00:07:23,680
You are ruining the reputation
of Grade 12 students.

93
00:07:26,040 --> 00:07:28,800
There’s no need to be serious about this.

94
00:07:29,480 --> 00:07:30,400
Fine, we’ll leave.

95
00:07:38,160 --> 00:07:39,560
Please follow the line.

96
00:08:00,400 --> 00:08:01,600
What’s wrong, Boss Ko?

97
00:08:04,640 --> 00:08:06,040
I just noticed something.

98
00:08:08,320 --> 00:08:09,080
Look.

99
00:08:10,080 --> 00:08:12,400
Everyone seems to have a boyfriend or a girlfriend.

100
00:08:13,880 --> 00:08:16,880
Some of them are in different classes.

101
00:08:17,600 --> 00:08:20,520
Some of them are in the same class,
but their seats are apart.

102
00:08:21,000 --> 00:08:24,920
But they are having lunch together.

103
00:08:25,480 --> 00:08:26,360
So what?

104
00:08:31,480 --> 00:08:32,920
I thought you would come to meet us tomorrow.

105
00:08:33,880 --> 00:08:38,280
You know? Achi just scolded senior students.

106
00:08:38,320 --> 00:08:41,800
He was waiting in line to buy his lunch.

107
00:08:42,000 --> 00:08:43,680
But Grade 12 students cut in line
in front of him.

108
00:08:43,680 --> 00:08:45,480
So he slapped them in the face.

109
00:08:45,800 --> 00:08:47,240
Damn, did he really slap them?

110
00:08:47,240 --> 00:08:48,200
He almost punched them.

111
00:08:48,680 --> 00:08:50,320
He hit them in the face.

112
00:08:50,320 --> 00:08:52,400
Achi, you are savage.

113
00:08:53,320 --> 00:08:55,120
Augar is exaggerating it.

114
00:08:55,760 --> 00:08:58,560
I just told them
that they were wrong to do that.

115
00:08:58,560 --> 00:09:01,400
Yeah, I just want to make it
sound more exciting.

116
00:09:02,800 --> 00:09:04,840
You read too much manga, Augar.

117
00:09:05,400 --> 00:09:06,040
Me?

118
00:09:07,240 --> 00:09:08,560
Are you sure?

119
00:09:11,840 --> 00:09:14,000
Don’t you feel good saying it out?

120
00:09:15,080 --> 00:09:15,640
Yeah.

121
00:09:15,960 --> 00:09:17,400
But I was a bit scared.

122
00:09:17,720 --> 00:09:18,920
There’s no need to be scared.

123
00:09:19,080 --> 00:09:20,120
You didn’t do anything wrong.

124
00:09:22,520 --> 00:09:23,680
Well done, Achi.

125
00:09:24,440 --> 00:09:27,680
You are brave.
That’s why you are in my gang.

126
00:09:27,680 --> 00:09:29,520
But the gang leader is a total mess.

127
00:09:29,520 --> 00:09:30,280
Augar!

128
00:09:31,000 --> 00:09:32,840
I’ll show you what I can do
when the chance comes.

129
00:09:33,200 --> 00:09:35,120
What are you up to now?

130
00:09:39,880 --> 00:09:43,240
I feel so good that we don’t have any classes
on the first day of school.

131
00:09:43,720 --> 00:09:45,160
Why don’t you come
to watch my basketball practice?

132
00:09:45,160 --> 00:09:47,240
Are you going to start the practice today?

133
00:09:47,320 --> 00:09:50,960
In our dad’s days,
Michael Jordan was the star.

134
00:09:51,320 --> 00:09:53,520
Now, it’s Kobe Bryant.

135
00:09:53,720 --> 00:09:56,240
Do you know who will be the star
in the next four years?

136
00:09:56,400 --> 00:09:56,720
Who?
Me.

137
00:09:59,200 --> 00:10:01,800
Damn, you are so cool.

138
00:10:01,800 --> 00:10:03,840
Augar, I know you can do it.

139
00:10:04,040 --> 00:10:06,360
You are blindly supporting him.

140
00:10:08,920 --> 00:10:10,320
But I think you can do it.

141
00:10:10,560 --> 00:10:11,800
You work hard.

142
00:10:13,920 --> 00:10:16,120
Me too. I think you can do it.

143
00:10:16,280 --> 00:10:17,680
But I just can’t stand you sometimes.

144
00:10:18,840 --> 00:10:20,000
Stop it, jackass.

145
00:10:20,200 --> 00:10:21,480
I’m going to eat my lunch. I’m hungry.

146
00:10:36,560 --> 00:10:38,920
Why are girls crazy about athletes, Ko Song?

147
00:10:40,080 --> 00:10:41,200
Do they look cool?

148
00:10:42,680 --> 00:10:43,480
I don’t know.

149
00:10:43,880 --> 00:10:46,520
Maybe they have this charm
of knowing what they want to do.

150
00:10:51,760 --> 00:10:52,960
What about you?

151
00:10:54,120 --> 00:10:55,240
Did you find what you like?

152
00:10:56,560 --> 00:10:58,640
Or do you have someone that you like?

153
00:11:00,920 --> 00:11:01,760
I don’t know.

154
00:11:02,360 --> 00:11:03,480
I only think about studying.

155
00:11:05,520 --> 00:11:06,480
That’s true.

156
00:11:10,920 --> 00:11:13,600
Ko Neung, did you find what you like?

157
00:11:20,960 --> 00:11:21,720
Ko Song.

158
00:11:22,680 --> 00:11:24,440
My friend asked me to give you this drink.

159
00:11:27,360 --> 00:11:30,440
Our friend with glasses has a secret admirer.

160
00:11:33,080 --> 00:11:37,280
Are you sure?
Did she say Ko Neung or Ko Song?

161
00:11:37,400 --> 00:11:39,680
Don’t forget to finish the glass, Ko Song.

162
00:11:41,160 --> 00:11:42,360
Thank you.

163
00:11:43,520 --> 00:11:45,240
Ko Song is so cute.

164
00:11:46,960 --> 00:11:48,320
Now, you’ve all grown up.

165
00:11:48,600 --> 00:11:50,160
You became popular, Ko Song.

166
00:11:51,160 --> 00:11:54,040
Ko Song, you are something.
An older girl has a crush on you.

167
00:11:54,280 --> 00:11:57,000
If you date her, please tell her that

168
00:11:57,160 --> 00:11:58,560
you have a friend named August.

169
00:11:58,840 --> 00:12:00,880
He is single.

170
00:12:01,080 --> 00:12:03,440
Stop it. I don’t even know who she is.

171
00:12:03,880 --> 00:12:04,640
Hey.

172
00:12:04,880 --> 00:12:06,440
Are you interested in her?

173
00:12:20,600 --> 00:12:21,520
I’m thirsty.

174
00:12:25,160 --> 00:12:25,680
Hey.

175
00:12:31,800 --> 00:12:32,760
Now I know…

176
00:12:33,520 --> 00:12:34,720
what I want to do.

177
00:12:39,160 --> 00:12:41,800
I want to date.

178
00:12:55,880 --> 00:12:56,520
Orange.

179
00:12:58,480 --> 00:12:59,840
Why do you want to date?

180
00:13:02,680 --> 00:13:03,680
Look at you guys.

181
00:13:03,680 --> 00:13:06,480
You have all grown up
and changed in your own ways.

182
00:13:08,880 --> 00:13:10,160
That’s why you want to date?

183
00:13:12,440 --> 00:13:15,200
Why? Can’t I date?

184
00:13:17,160 --> 00:13:17,960
No.

185
00:13:18,840 --> 00:13:19,880
I have no problem with it.

186
00:13:20,640 --> 00:13:21,960
I’m just curious.

187
00:13:23,680 --> 00:13:26,200
Or you don’t want me to date anyone?

188
00:13:32,160 --> 00:13:33,040
No.

189
00:13:34,960 --> 00:13:35,600
Right?

190
00:13:36,120 --> 00:13:37,960
You’re afraid that
you have to go home alone, right?

191
00:13:41,880 --> 00:13:45,480
No, I just feel for your date
for having a silly boyfriend.

192
00:13:46,280 --> 00:13:47,120
Boo!

193
00:13:47,320 --> 00:13:49,200
Ko Song, get back here.

194
00:13:49,440 --> 00:13:50,600
I forgot my bag.

195
00:13:51,600 --> 00:13:52,920
Come back.

196
00:13:53,840 --> 00:13:54,640
Come back.

197
00:13:54,960 --> 00:13:55,680
You can’t run away from me.

198
00:14:01,960 --> 00:14:03,120
Do I need to close the door?

199
00:14:03,360 --> 00:14:04,000
Yes.

200
00:14:09,800 --> 00:14:11,280
Damn, can I use your computer?

201
00:14:11,840 --> 00:14:14,080
I really want to use it. Please, please.

202
00:14:14,320 --> 00:14:15,040
Yeah.

203
00:14:15,840 --> 00:14:17,880
I won’t sleep tonight.

204
00:14:19,320 --> 00:14:20,680
Aren’t your parents home?

205
00:14:22,760 --> 00:14:23,680
They are probably upstairs.

206
00:14:29,040 --> 00:14:31,920
Your house always looks like nobody is home.

207
00:14:33,440 --> 00:14:34,720
If it’s my house,

208
00:14:34,880 --> 00:14:37,200
I haven’t even stepped into the house,

209
00:14:37,200 --> 00:14:39,320
my mom already told me to take a shower.

210
00:14:40,080 --> 00:14:41,240
It’s so boring.

211
00:14:41,240 --> 00:14:42,600
My house is more boring.

212
00:14:45,720 --> 00:14:46,480
Really?

213
00:14:48,040 --> 00:14:49,280
I guess they are boring in different ways.

214
00:14:53,000 --> 00:14:54,160
Your house is lively.

215
00:14:54,840 --> 00:14:57,080
You are close to your parents.

216
00:14:57,840 --> 00:14:59,600
That’s why you are a cheerful person.

217
00:15:05,400 --> 00:15:06,000
Maybe.
I don’t know.

218
00:15:10,600 --> 00:15:12,160
I’ll play games.

219
00:15:19,160 --> 00:15:21,800
I got it. I got it.

220
00:15:24,080 --> 00:15:25,800
Damn, I’m dead.

221
00:15:26,480 --> 00:15:27,840
What the heck?

222
00:15:28,200 --> 00:15:29,680
I just started, but I’m already killed.

223
00:15:30,360 --> 00:15:31,080
Look.

224
00:15:31,800 --> 00:15:32,680
Hello, Dad.

225
00:15:34,560 --> 00:15:35,720
When did you get home?

226
00:15:36,440 --> 00:15:37,520
7.30 p.m.

227
00:15:38,880 --> 00:15:39,880
You’ve been home for a while.

228
00:15:39,880 --> 00:15:40,920
Why haven’t you taken a shower yet?

229
00:15:43,200 --> 00:15:44,720
You need to go to bed at 10 p.m.

230
00:15:44,960 --> 00:15:46,000
You have to go to school tomorrow.

231
00:15:47,080 --> 00:15:47,960
Yes, Dad.

232
00:15:50,640 --> 00:15:51,400
Goodbye.

233
00:15:55,520 --> 00:15:57,200
Orange, you can continue to play the game.

234
00:15:57,840 --> 00:15:59,440
My dad only came downstairs this time.

235
00:16:00,040 --> 00:16:01,720
He will come down again in the morning.

236
00:16:04,880 --> 00:16:06,040
I don’t think it’s a good idea.

237
00:16:08,040 --> 00:16:10,040
Don’t you see his icy glare?

238
00:16:10,640 --> 00:16:12,040
I should go home now.

239
00:16:12,520 --> 00:16:13,280
Okay.

240
00:16:20,280 --> 00:16:21,120
Thanks.

241
00:16:23,240 --> 00:16:24,120
Thanks for what?

242
00:16:24,120 --> 00:16:25,600
For playing games at my house.

243
00:16:27,280 --> 00:16:28,640
If you didn’t come here,

244
00:16:29,360 --> 00:16:31,240
my house would be very quiet.

245
00:16:37,840 --> 00:16:38,640
How about this?

246
00:16:39,080 --> 00:16:42,160
You go to my house in the morning.

247
00:16:42,520 --> 00:16:45,320
I’ll come to your house in the evening.

248
00:16:47,120 --> 00:16:47,880
What do you think?

249
00:16:48,600 --> 00:16:50,320
It’s fair, right?

250
00:16:54,720 --> 00:16:55,720
I’ll think about it.

251
00:16:59,760 --> 00:17:00,360
Okay.

252
00:17:00,600 --> 00:17:01,440
I’m leaving.

253
00:17:04,960 --> 00:17:05,480
Hey.

254
00:17:06,320 --> 00:17:07,640
If you want to talk to me.

255
00:17:12,200 --> 00:17:12,880
See you.

256
00:17:13,360 --> 00:17:14,120
Bye.

257
00:17:32,240 --> 00:17:34,200
Here comes the hot soup.

258
00:17:35,160 --> 00:17:36,080
Have a seat.

259
00:17:38,480 --> 00:17:41,600
Here is your favorite. I remember.

260
00:17:43,480 --> 00:17:44,320
Good.

261
00:17:44,640 --> 00:17:48,320
I’m heading out to the sea soon.
Do you want…

262
00:17:48,320 --> 00:17:48,880
No.

263
00:17:49,760 --> 00:17:52,120
Ko, can you let me finish first?

264
00:17:52,200 --> 00:17:53,640
Why are you mentioning it?

265
00:17:53,720 --> 00:17:56,280
You can use minors under 18
as your laborers.

266
00:17:56,760 --> 00:17:58,880
Otherwise, I’ll report you
to the Department of Labor.

267
00:18:00,200 --> 00:18:02,200
Am I dreaming, honey?

268
00:18:02,560 --> 00:18:04,800
Our son has all grown up.

269
00:18:04,800 --> 00:18:05,760
He even knows this stuff.

270
00:18:05,960 --> 00:18:07,480
He’s now in Grade 11.

271
00:18:07,760 --> 00:18:09,240
Of course.

272
00:18:09,600 --> 00:18:10,400
Do you have a girlfriend?

273
00:18:13,120 --> 00:18:14,520
What girlfriend? No.

274
00:18:15,840 --> 00:18:16,880
Didn’t you say you wanted to…

275
00:18:16,880 --> 00:18:17,680
What, Ko?

276
00:18:18,440 --> 00:18:21,680
Tell me now.

277
00:18:21,680 --> 00:18:22,840
I have nothing to tell you, Mom.

278
00:18:22,840 --> 00:18:24,160
I don’t have a girlfriend.

279
00:18:28,040 --> 00:18:29,720
He doesn’t have a girlfriend, but he wants to.

280
00:18:34,120 --> 00:18:34,960
Mom.

281
00:18:35,920 --> 00:18:38,680
Is it that strange if I want to date?

282
00:18:39,280 --> 00:18:40,600
I’m not saying anything.

283
00:18:40,600 --> 00:18:41,280
Yeah.

284
00:18:42,840 --> 00:18:46,760
Dad, I’m curious
what kind of boyfriend he will be.

285
00:18:47,560 --> 00:18:48,520
Don’t worry, Mom.

286
00:18:48,680 --> 00:18:50,080
If I’m dating,

287
00:18:50,960 --> 00:18:53,520
I will introduce that person to you.

288
00:18:53,960 --> 00:18:55,360
You will bring her home?

289
00:18:55,400 --> 00:18:56,200
Yes.

290
00:18:56,200 --> 00:18:57,800
Then what?

291
00:18:58,480 --> 00:19:00,480
So you guys can get to know each other.

292
00:19:00,480 --> 00:19:03,720
What are you going to do? Show me.

293
00:19:04,000 --> 00:19:04,880
Yes, show me.

294
00:19:16,240 --> 00:19:17,200
Dad.

295
00:19:17,440 --> 00:19:18,400
Mom.

296
00:19:18,680 --> 00:19:21,560
This is Ko Song, my boyfriend.

297
00:19:29,520 --> 00:19:31,600
Who are your parents?

298
00:19:32,520 --> 00:19:35,360
Mom, you’re watching too much soap opera.

299
00:19:37,680 --> 00:19:38,640
Fine. I’ll start again.

300
00:19:39,600 --> 00:19:41,000
What do you like to eat?

301
00:19:41,120 --> 00:19:42,440
I like winter melon soup.

302
00:19:49,320 --> 00:19:50,640
What, Mom? Just say it.

303
00:19:50,640 --> 00:19:52,520
How would I know what you want me to do?

304
00:19:53,720 --> 00:19:55,000
You fail it.

305
00:19:55,920 --> 00:19:59,440
She tries to tell you to put food on his plate.

306
00:19:59,440 --> 00:20:01,160
Yes, Ko.

307
00:20:01,160 --> 00:20:04,720
This is important. You can’t forget it.

308
00:20:04,720 --> 00:20:05,720
Look at your dad.

309
00:20:05,960 --> 00:20:07,960
He always does that for me.

310
00:20:08,040 --> 00:20:10,480
It’s not a big deal.
This is just a hypothetical scenario.

311
00:20:25,920 --> 00:20:28,000
Here is your winter melon.

312
00:20:29,560 --> 00:20:32,240
Please enjoy it, Ko Song.

313
00:20:43,920 --> 00:20:45,880
Well done, sweetie.

314
00:20:46,040 --> 00:20:50,200
I’m so proud of you, my son.

315
00:20:51,080 --> 00:20:53,240
You are too into this story.

316
00:21:03,760 --> 00:21:08,040
We are going to learn about internal organs today.

317
00:21:08,040 --> 00:21:09,160
Please open your book.

318
00:21:10,280 --> 00:21:10,880
Krittin.

319
00:21:12,880 --> 00:21:13,520
Yes.

320
00:21:14,320 --> 00:21:15,120
Stand up.

321
00:21:18,080 --> 00:21:19,320
Do you really like oranges?

322
00:21:20,400 --> 00:21:21,000
Stand on one leg.

323
00:21:22,440 --> 00:21:23,840
Put the orange on your head.

324
00:21:24,440 --> 00:21:26,080
What orange are you talking about?

325
00:21:34,400 --> 00:21:34,960
Do it.

326
00:21:35,400 --> 00:21:36,840
I’m sorry.

327
00:21:41,080 --> 00:21:42,600
Everyone, turn to the next page.

328
00:21:42,840 --> 00:21:45,320
Mr. Kong, do I have to stand until the end of the class?

329
00:21:45,320 --> 00:21:49,320
I’ll give you ten minutes to read this page.

330
00:21:53,040 --> 00:21:54,160
Let’s read together.

331
00:21:59,040 --> 00:21:59,520
Ko Song.

332
00:22:01,040 --> 00:22:01,560
Ko Song.
What?

333
00:22:02,440 --> 00:22:03,160
Stop talking.

334
00:22:03,480 --> 00:22:04,320
Otherwise, you will be punished again.

335
00:22:07,120 --> 00:22:08,000
My shorts.

336
00:22:08,400 --> 00:22:09,080
What?

337
00:22:09,640 --> 00:22:10,640
Don’t laugh at me.

338
00:22:10,880 --> 00:22:12,080
What are you talking about?

339
00:22:12,320 --> 00:22:14,000
Can you pull my shorts?

340
00:22:14,160 --> 00:22:15,280
I’m studying.

341
00:22:15,560 --> 00:22:17,960
I have a wedgie. It’s itchy. Come on, help me.

342
00:22:26,320 --> 00:22:26,960
Are you serious?

343
00:22:27,040 --> 00:22:28,920
Come on. It’s itchy.

344
00:22:29,400 --> 00:22:30,080
Okay, okay.

345
00:22:40,440 --> 00:22:41,320
What a relief!

346
00:22:45,200 --> 00:22:51,600
Next week, we will have a quiz and a school trip.

347
00:22:54,480 --> 00:22:55,760
What?

348
00:22:56,160 --> 00:22:58,240
You don’t even know where we are going,
but you already get excited.

349
00:22:58,400 --> 00:22:59,840
So where are we going?

350
00:23:01,400 --> 00:23:03,560
Mangrove forest.

351
00:23:06,920 --> 00:23:09,760
Mr. Kong, why don’t we go to Bangkok?

352
00:23:09,840 --> 00:23:12,120
A place with air conditioning
where we can spend time comfortably.

353
00:23:13,040 --> 00:23:15,320
Kids these days.

354
00:23:16,400 --> 00:23:17,560
I can go anywhere.

355
00:23:18,680 --> 00:23:20,720
But right now, can I sit down first?

356
00:23:30,800 --> 00:23:32,560
Everyone, let’s get back to our lesson.

357
00:23:34,400 --> 00:23:35,480
My butt hurts.

358
00:23:37,080 --> 00:23:38,560
Why didn’t you hurry and pull it? It was so itchy.

359
00:23:39,480 --> 00:23:41,520
Because of the wedgie,
I now want to go to the bathroom.

360
00:23:47,640 --> 00:23:48,480
Why are you smiling?

361
00:23:49,720 --> 00:23:50,440
Nothing.

362
00:24:01,920 --> 00:24:02,720
Guys.

363
00:24:03,480 --> 00:24:04,800
I have something to show you.

364
00:24:06,760 --> 00:24:09,200
I prepared lots of snacks today.

365
00:24:11,800 --> 00:24:14,560
So your bag is fat because of the snacks?

366
00:24:15,160 --> 00:24:16,520
What else do you think would be in my bag?

367
00:24:17,440 --> 00:24:18,320
Just eat it.

368
00:24:18,440 --> 00:24:21,200
Just pick anything that you like.

369
00:24:23,000 --> 00:24:23,520
Give me some.
Here.

370
00:24:26,120 --> 00:24:27,120
Look, Tle.

371
00:24:27,840 --> 00:24:28,760
This is how you eat it.

372
00:24:32,040 --> 00:24:34,800
If you eat a snack in the morning, it will spike your blood sugar.

373
00:24:37,880 --> 00:24:39,040
Just eat it.

374
00:24:39,400 --> 00:24:41,440
I’ve been putting up with your stomach growling for a while.

375
00:24:45,520 --> 00:24:46,120
It’s delicious.

376
00:24:47,000 --> 00:24:47,880
Aren’t you excited?

377
00:24:49,120 --> 00:24:49,800
Yes.

378
00:24:50,400 --> 00:24:51,840
But the teacher said the sunlight is strong today.

379
00:24:53,280 --> 00:24:54,400
Are you Dracula?

380
00:24:55,160 --> 00:24:55,600
What?

381
00:25:03,400 --> 00:25:04,320
Come to think about it.

382
00:25:05,400 --> 00:25:06,920
This is our first trip together.

383
00:25:11,440 --> 00:25:11,640
Huh?

384
00:25:14,160 --> 00:25:14,720
What did you say?

385
00:25:18,040 --> 00:25:19,440
This is our first trip together.

386
00:25:20,320 --> 00:25:20,800
Do you like it?

387
00:25:26,920 --> 00:25:28,440
I’ll tell you when we get home.

388
00:25:32,360 --> 00:25:33,160
Fine.

389
00:25:36,960 --> 00:25:39,080
Guys, shall I open a new snack bag?

390
00:25:39,560 --> 00:25:41,080
Sure.

391
00:25:43,240 --> 00:25:44,200
Damn.

392
00:25:45,560 --> 00:25:46,760
It serves you right.

393
00:25:58,160 --> 00:25:59,160
Everyone, get off the bus.

394
00:26:01,360 --> 00:26:02,520
Everyone, stay orderly, please.

395
00:26:04,000 --> 00:26:04,840
Let’s go, Ko Song.

396
00:26:05,640 --> 00:26:06,880
Come on, Ko Song.

397
00:26:06,920 --> 00:26:07,600
Don’t run.

398
00:26:08,760 --> 00:26:09,640
Stay in a line.

399
00:26:11,680 --> 00:26:13,760
Guys, let’s have fun in the mud.

400
00:26:14,040 --> 00:26:15,280
Let’s go.

401
00:26:18,520 --> 00:26:19,960
Hold on, Krittin.

402
00:26:19,960 --> 00:26:20,440
Yes.

403
00:26:20,680 --> 00:26:22,320
Don’t do anything crazy.

404
00:26:23,120 --> 00:26:24,600
Yes, sir.

405
00:26:25,600 --> 00:26:28,080
Go. Follow your friends.

406
00:26:28,080 --> 00:26:30,800
Tle, please help me monitor them.

407
00:26:31,280 --> 00:26:31,640
Sure.

408
00:26:33,040 --> 00:26:36,640
It’s so refreshing.

409
00:26:42,960 --> 00:26:44,520
Why do you look so grumpy?

410
00:26:44,520 --> 00:26:45,640
Come out and feel the sunlight.

411
00:26:47,120 --> 00:26:47,680
Ko Neung.
Huh?

412
00:26:48,720 --> 00:26:51,360
The best time to go out in the sun is 6 – 9 a.m.

413
00:26:52,040 --> 00:26:53,320
Right now, it’s dangerous to be exposed to the sun.

414
00:26:55,400 --> 00:26:55,760
What?

415
00:26:56,720 --> 00:26:58,120
So what are we doing here at this hour?

416
00:26:58,360 --> 00:26:59,600
Are you stupid?

417
00:27:00,240 --> 00:27:02,120
Our meeting time at school is 8 a.m.

418
00:27:02,280 --> 00:27:04,360
With the traveling, that’s why we got here now.

419
00:27:06,480 --> 00:27:07,960
Do you want to compete with me, Augar?

420
00:27:09,280 --> 00:27:10,640
Who can plant more saplings?

421
00:27:11,000 --> 00:27:13,160
You dare to compete with me, the god of competition?

422
00:27:13,200 --> 00:27:13,640
Yes.

423
00:27:13,680 --> 00:27:15,320
You got a deal.

424
00:27:15,400 --> 00:27:16,560
How dare you call yourself that?

425
00:27:16,880 --> 00:27:17,520
What about you, August?

426
00:27:18,160 --> 00:27:20,040
Just leave me out.

427
00:27:20,760 --> 00:27:22,160
I’ll be with Ko Song and Achi.

428
00:27:22,920 --> 00:27:24,600
I’m not an energetic folk like you.

429
00:27:32,240 --> 00:27:32,760
Wear this.
Augar.

430
00:27:35,040 --> 00:27:35,640
Take it.

431
00:27:38,360 --> 00:27:39,200
It’s okay.

432
00:27:41,920 --> 00:27:42,880
Wear it.

433
00:27:43,760 --> 00:27:45,280
You look so pale.

434
00:27:45,720 --> 00:27:46,360
Stop arguing with me.

435
00:27:48,200 --> 00:27:49,040
He doesn’t look pale.

436
00:27:49,320 --> 00:27:50,120
His face is all red.

437
00:28:00,040 --> 00:28:02,360
I’m sensitive to sunlight.

438
00:28:02,800 --> 00:28:04,520
That’s right.

439
00:28:05,960 --> 00:28:09,120
Damn, me too.

440
00:28:09,760 --> 00:28:11,760
I should wait in an air-conditioned room.

441
00:28:19,480 --> 00:28:21,600
Ko Song, can you take a picture for me?

442
00:28:22,080 --> 00:28:25,000
Damn, why didn’t we bring a camera?

443
00:28:25,600 --> 00:28:26,280
That’s right.

444
00:28:26,880 --> 00:28:27,880
I want to have a picture too.

445
00:28:37,240 --> 00:28:38,160
Get closer.

446
00:28:39,880 --> 00:28:40,720
Tle.

447
00:28:41,920 --> 00:28:43,120
Can you take a picture for us?

448
00:28:43,120 --> 00:28:44,280
I want to have a picture too.

449
00:28:44,280 --> 00:28:45,240
Just one picture.

450
00:28:45,760 --> 00:28:47,280
It’s not my camera.

451
00:28:47,560 --> 00:28:49,520
You need to wait to ask the owner.

452
00:28:50,040 --> 00:28:51,520
Come on, Tle.

453
00:28:52,040 --> 00:28:53,800
Can you take a picture for me?

454
00:28:55,840 --> 00:28:56,360
Okay.

455
00:28:56,920 --> 00:28:57,280
Huh?

456
00:28:59,680 --> 00:29:01,280
But you just said no to me.

457
00:29:01,880 --> 00:29:02,720
Come here, Ko Song.

458
00:29:03,320 --> 00:29:05,480
You have a double standard.

459
00:29:06,160 --> 00:29:06,600
Ready?

460
00:29:07,320 --> 00:29:09,560
One, two, three.

461
00:29:53,720 --> 00:29:55,440
Since you did a great job today.

462
00:29:55,440 --> 00:29:57,880
Your teacher wants to give you a reward.

463
00:29:57,880 --> 00:29:59,880
You will have free time for one hour.

464
00:30:00,040 --> 00:30:00,920
Let’s jump into the sea.

465
00:30:01,160 --> 00:30:01,840
Sure.

466
00:30:07,280 --> 00:30:08,640
We’ve been living in a beach town,

467
00:30:09,080 --> 00:30:10,560
but we’ve never gone to the beach together.

468
00:30:11,520 --> 00:30:12,680
So this will be their hazing.

469
00:30:14,040 --> 00:30:15,360
Shall we?

470
00:30:16,080 --> 00:30:16,760
What do you mean?

471
00:30:17,560 --> 00:30:20,120
August, you take his right. I’ll take his left.

472
00:30:21,640 --> 00:30:23,120
Augar, can you handle it alone?

473
00:30:23,400 --> 00:30:24,120
No problem.

474
00:30:24,280 --> 00:30:25,600
What are you doing? I want to do it too.

475
00:30:26,640 --> 00:30:29,200
August, three, two, one, go.

476
00:30:41,760 --> 00:30:43,040
Wait.

477
00:30:43,600 --> 00:30:44,840
I can’t swim.

478
00:30:45,480 --> 00:30:46,400
Don’t worry.

479
00:30:46,840 --> 00:30:47,480
Trust me.

480
00:30:48,480 --> 00:30:49,320
Okay.

481
00:30:49,840 --> 00:30:53,320
♪ Every time that we meet again ♪

482
00:30:53,320 --> 00:30:57,360
♪ Something grows a little more each day ♪

483
00:30:57,360 --> 00:31:02,080
♪ The closer we are, the more I feel the love I’ve waited for ♪

484
00:31:02,080 --> 00:31:04,640
♪ Might not be too far away at all ♪

485
00:31:04,640 --> 00:31:05,240
My eyes hurt.

486
00:31:05,240 --> 00:31:09,240
♪ Even when winter fades I’ll still wait on ♪

487
00:31:09,240 --> 00:31:13,280
♪ Till the final raindrop falls, hope is never gone ♪

488
00:31:13,280 --> 00:31:17,600
♪ As long as I have you holding my hand as we walk on ♪

489
00:31:17,600 --> 00:31:24,200
♪ I fear nothing if this season has you ♪

490
00:32:07,400 --> 00:32:08,880
I got the answer.

491
00:32:11,880 --> 00:32:14,720
You asked me if I like that we take a trip together.

492
00:32:20,240 --> 00:32:21,200
I really like it.

493
00:32:40,760 --> 00:32:42,640
Why am I always the only one who sees it?

494
00:33:07,360 --> 00:33:08,880
Wow!

495
00:33:09,720 --> 00:33:12,000
This is so cool, Ko.

496
00:33:12,160 --> 00:33:13,120
Do you like it that much?

497
00:33:14,640 --> 00:33:16,680
I don’t want to go to an internet café.

498
00:33:18,200 --> 00:33:19,680
You can come to use it every day.

499
00:33:20,360 --> 00:33:21,760
No, I don’t want to bother you.

500
00:33:22,520 --> 00:33:23,240
It’s not a big deal.

501
00:33:37,520 --> 00:33:38,200
Are you going to sleep?

502
00:33:39,080 --> 00:33:39,840
I’m tired.

503
00:33:40,400 --> 00:33:42,320
I’m going to rest my eyes for 20 minutes.

504
00:33:43,560 --> 00:33:45,160
But you can play the games.

505
00:33:45,680 --> 00:33:46,360
It’s okay to turn on the speaker.

506
00:33:51,640 --> 00:33:52,760
20 minutes?

507
00:33:53,040 --> 00:33:53,960
I have tried it.

508
00:33:54,280 --> 00:33:56,720
I wanted to briefly rest my eyes,
but I ended up sleeping through the night.

509
00:34:04,720 --> 00:34:06,920
Damn it. I’m dead.

510
00:34:08,160 --> 00:34:09,040
What the heck?

511
00:34:14,480 --> 00:34:15,600
Damn it.

512
00:34:30,280 --> 00:34:31,200
Damn it.

513
00:34:31,920 --> 00:34:32,960
You seem to have fun with it.

514
00:34:36,920 --> 00:34:38,720
I thought you were sleeping.

515
00:34:39,760 --> 00:34:41,600
I told you I just rested my eyes.

516
00:34:42,520 --> 00:34:44,040
I do it often while studying.

517
00:34:47,520 --> 00:34:50,560
Studying is so boring, Ko Song.

518
00:34:54,080 --> 00:34:56,080
I’m not surprised. You don’t like studying.

519
00:35:03,600 --> 00:35:05,160
I’m tired of playing games.

520
00:35:05,160 --> 00:35:08,280
Do you have anything else for me to do?

521
00:35:11,960 --> 00:35:12,760
What?

522
00:35:13,360 --> 00:35:14,640
I’m bored.

523
00:35:14,640 --> 00:35:16,800
I’m bored. I’m bored. I’m bored.

524
00:35:17,360 --> 00:35:19,040
Don’t you have something new to do?

525
00:35:20,080 --> 00:35:21,160
If you’re bored, why don’t you go home?

526
00:35:22,000 --> 00:35:22,760
Or do you want to sleep over here?

527
00:35:24,840 --> 00:35:26,120
No.

528
00:35:26,720 --> 00:35:28,200
Can’t you find something for me to play?

529
00:35:30,760 --> 00:35:31,400
Do you want to eat oranges?

530
00:35:32,400 --> 00:35:34,040
I already ate it today. I’ve had enough.

531
00:35:55,280 --> 00:35:56,520
What is it, Ko Song?

532
00:35:57,080 --> 00:35:57,640
What is it?

533
00:36:01,000 --> 00:36:02,000
Let me see.

534
00:36:05,440 --> 00:36:06,720
How does it work?

535
00:36:09,080 --> 00:36:10,720
Am I smart enough to play it?

536
00:37:02,440 --> 00:37:03,200
Ko Song.

537
00:37:05,520 --> 00:37:06,360
Come on.

538
00:37:09,680 --> 00:37:10,840
Come here.

539
00:37:17,400 --> 00:37:18,440
Choose a number.

540
00:37:20,240 --> 00:37:21,120
What is this?

541
00:37:22,560 --> 00:37:24,840
Come on. Choose a number.

542
00:37:25,800 --> 00:37:26,280
One.

543
00:37:26,880 --> 00:37:27,560
How many times?

544
00:37:28,480 --> 00:37:29,000
10 times.

545
00:37:29,800 --> 00:37:30,440
Here we go.

546
00:37:31,480 --> 00:37:34,880
One, two, three, four, five, six, seven, eight, nine, ten.

547
00:37:42,120 --> 00:37:42,880
What?

548
00:37:44,040 --> 00:37:45,800
Be careful.

549
00:37:47,000 --> 00:37:47,600
Say it.

550
00:37:49,840 --> 00:37:52,480
Be careful. Your friend might become your date.

551
00:37:57,160 --> 00:37:58,680
Which friend will it be?

552
00:37:59,160 --> 00:38:00,400
Many of our classmates have a crush on you.

553
00:38:00,880 --> 00:38:02,000
Some kids from other classes also like you.

554
00:38:03,160 --> 00:38:06,520
You are quite popular these days.

555
00:38:13,680 --> 00:38:16,200
Silly. It’s just nonsense.

556
